				<p>What can be described in a system with an axis and the magnitudes vector along the axis is a SCREW. From the [Summer Screw](http://www.dimec.unige.it/PMAR/summer_screws/SS09/PDF/Part1/SS09-Zlatanov.pdf) page 19 : a line l with a pitch h (a metric quantity) is a geometric element called a screw. A wrench is a system of forces (reduced at a point) with equivalent systems identified.</p>
