				<p><p>Summarizing from <a href="http://www.cds.caltech.edu/~murray/mlswiki/index.php/Main_Page" rel="nofollow">Murray, Li, and Sastry</a> (chapters 3 and 5) there are 3 related things:</p>

<ul>
<li>Twist: An element of se(3) (which is a bit like the derivative of an element of SE(3), which is the set of translations + rotations)</li>
<li>Screw: A translation+rotation (i.e. and element of SE(3))</li>
<li>Wrench: Generalized force (combination of linear force and torque)</li>
</ul>
</p><br>
